  "sections": [
    {
      "id": "hazard-awareness",
      "title": "Hazard Awareness",
      "order": 1,
      "estMin": 25,
      "lessons": [
        {
          "id": "recognize-hazards",
          "title": "Recognize Common Hazards",
          "order": 1,
          "estMin": 12,
          "blocks": [
            {
              "id": "text",
              "type": "text",
              "html": "<p>Hazards can include wet floors, blocked exits, poor lighting, unsafe equipment, exposed cords, heavy lifting, chemical exposure, and workplace violence risks.</p><p>Employees should pause, identify risks, and follow the reporting process before a hazard becomes an incident.</p>",
              "required": true
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "prevent-injuries",
          "title": "Prevent Common Injuries",
          "order": 2,
          "estMin": 13,
          "blocks": [
            {
              "id": "text",
              "type": "text",
              "html": "<ul><li>Keep walkways clear.</li><li>Use proper lifting technique.</li><li>Report damaged equipment.</li><li>Wear required protective equipment.</li><li>Follow lockout or access rules where applicable.</li></ul>",
              "required": true
            },
            {
              "id": "quiz",
              "type": "quiz",
              "mode": "single",
              "question": "What should an employee do when a hazard is found?",
              "required": true,
              "choices": [
                {
                  "id": "a",
                  "text": "Ignore it if nobody was injured",
                  "correct": false
                },
                {
                  "id": "b",
                  "text": "Report it using the approved process",
                  "correct": true
                },
                {
                  "id": "c",
                  "text": "Post about it publicly",
                  "correct": false
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "emergency-response",
      "title": "Emergency Response and Reporting",
      "order": 2,
      "estMin": 25,
      "lessons": [
        {
          "id": "incident-reporting",
          "title": "Incident and Near-Miss Reporting",
          "order": 1,
          "estMin": 12,
          "blocks": [
            {
              "id": "text",
              "type": "text",
              "html": "<p>A near miss is a warning sign. Reporting near misses helps the organization correct hazards before a serious injury occurs.</p>",
              "required": true
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "emergency-basics",
          "title": "Emergency Basics",
          "order": 2,
          "estMin": 13,
          "blocks": [
            {
              "id": "callout",
              "type": "callout",
              "style": "warn",
              "html": "<p>Know evacuation routes, assembly points, emergency contacts, and when to call emergency services.</p>",
              "required": true
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
